    "The underlying reason is straightforward.",
    "The musical score, ingeniously devised by humans, inherently encodes musical repetition.",
    "With just a repeat sign denoted as |: and:|, repeating phrases or even entire sections can be succinctly notated, corresponding to durations ranging from several seconds to minutes.",
    "See Contributions and Acknowledgments section for full author list.",
    "The ability to estimate the varying harmonies, keys, rhythms, and other musical elements that are not explicitly annotated in a piece of music and are significant for music themes, progression, and styles is called Music Reasoning."
